h3. Summary:

Look and feel section does provide a way to change header strip background colour from default blue to any other available colour, but does not adjust or provide a way to set search box colour ratio for it to be visible in same way as default after choosing the new header colour.

h3. Expected Result:

Search box(that lies in header as well) colour should automatically adjust the colour ratio per the selected header colour.

h3. Actual Result:

Let's say an organization has logo with white background and would like to switch the header colour to while. This is how the contrast looks like:
 !Screenshot 2021-03-19 at 3.19.31 PM.png|thumbnail! 
 !Screenshot 2021-03-19 at 3.21.56 PM.png|thumbnail! 

h3. Workaround:

Manual update on banner using script like below:

{code:java}
<script type="text/javascript">
function rgb2hex(rgb){
 rgb = rgb.match(/^rgba?[\s+]?\([\s+]?(\d+)[\s+]?,[\s+]?(\d+)[\s+]?,[\s+]?(\d+)[\s+]?/i);
 return (rgb && rgb.length === 4) ? "#" +
  ("0" + parseInt(rgb[1],10).toString(16)).slice(-2) +
  ("0" + parseInt(rgb[2],10).toString(16)).slice(-2) +
  ("0" + parseInt(rgb[3],10).toString(16)).slice(-2) : '';
}
if(rgb2hex($('#header > nav').css('background-color'))=='#ffffff'){$('#quickSearchInput').css('background-color','#ccc');}
else{console.log('current color is '+$('#header > nav').css('background-color'))}
</script>
{code}

