A user asks:

> Is there a quick way of bulk changing the resolution of issues in a
> project? I basically forgot to include the "Resolve issue" screen from
> our project's "Resolved" transition in the workflow, and there are
> thus no resolutions for the recently resolved issues...

Assuming that the user has the 'Resolve' and 'Edit' permissions, I can't see why the resolution shouldn't be editable.

{panel:title=Workaround}Please try the workaround listed here: [HowTo: Bulk Edit Resolution|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRAKB/HowTo%3A+Bulk+Edit+Resolution]{panel}

In the document [https://confluence.atlassian.com/jirasoftware/jira-software-8-13-x-upgrade-notes-1018783378.html], in the section *Known issue: Jira doesn’t recognize a MySQL database after the upgrade*, where it states
{quote}If you're using MySQL 5.6, you will need to upgrade your database first, as this version is no longer supported.{quote}
Please add a note saying that the {{utf8_bin}} collation/{{utf8}} charset has to be converted to {{utf8mb4_bin}}/{{utf8mb4}}. there's a KB with the steps at https://confluence.atlassian.com/kb/how-to-fix-the-collation-and-character-set-of-a-mysql-database-manually-744326173.html
